{
  "texts": [
    "By structural information, we denote the presence of activities, events, and gateways within the process model, whereas behavioral information encompasses details concerning the sequence flows linking these entities.",
    "QueryingThis phase includes the following steps: Retrieval and Answering.",
    "RetrievalIn this stage, the relevant process model chunks useful to generate accurate and contextually relevant answers to the user queries are retrieved.",
    "This component has been implemented by integrating the vector store (qDrant) within a retriever component (the RetrievalQA chain provided by Langchain).",
    "The RetrievalQA chain serves as the backbone for our retrieval process."
  ]
}